    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-28T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="418"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.796/249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-28T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 28, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>594. Reference despatch 4600, March 27 and previous regarding Corporación
                    Sudamericana de Servicios Aéreos. We have now postponed Proclaimed List
                    consideration for twice the period originally suggested in January by Dr. Bosch
                    and unless there is a more hopeful prospect of early complete elimination of
                    Axis interest in this company than appears to us here, we believe it will be
                    necessary to propose firm’s inclusion on list shortly.</p>
                <pb facs="0449" n="437" xml:id="pg_437"/>
                <p>Please report precise role occupied by Castillo Jr. in situation and whether you
                    now agree that foregoing action is necessary. For your confidential information,
                    our lack of action on this case has been commented on in high Brazilian official
                    circles.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
